A Metrorail train collided with a truck in Eerste River‚ Cape Town‚ on Wednesday causing 30-minute delays on the city's northern line. Metrorail spokesperson Rianna Scott confirmed the incident‚ which happened just after 8am. The 7.17am train from Muldersvlei to Cape Town and a tweet by Metrorail said it collided with the truck at the Eerste River level crossing.